<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="285" type="distribution and records">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="285">Distribution and Records.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="285">
<taxonomicName authority="Champion, 1888" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Charisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Charisius salvini" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salvini">Charisius salvini</taxonomicName>
was previously known from the highlands of southeastern and southcentral Guatemala. The species is now known to be widespread in Guatemala and is reported from El Salvador, Honduras and Nicaragua at elevations between 1340 and 1830 meters in elevation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="285">EL SALVADOR: Cerro Verde, 2000 m, 1.V. and 4.V.1971, HF Howden (CMNC, JMCC) 3.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="285">
